      "CVE": "CVE-2017-20230",
      "Description": "Storable versions before 3.05 for Perl has a stack overflow.\n\nThe retrieve_hook function stored the length of the class name into a signed integer but in read operations treated the length as unsigned. This allowed an attacker to craft data that could trigger the overflow.",
